engineer","digital nomad"],"logo":"","description":"<p>DraftKings is a leading sports entertainment brand that creates the most exciting digital sports competitions and experiences on the planet. Our goal is to transform the way fans experience sports. Our mission is to make sports better &ndash; and make better sports fans &ndash; by bringing them closer to the games they love. We are the signature tech startup of our generation in Boston.<\/p><br \/><p>DraftKings is seeking a Senior Software Engineer to join our engineering team.&nbsp; You will be developing systems and APIs that power a rich set of applications used by a large and passionate group of users every day. Your ability to create scalable, maintainable and performant software is critical to the success of the entire company. In your role, you will be deeply engaged in the entire Agile development lifecycle from design and implementation to testing and monitoring. We are looking for team players who are able to deliver imaginative solutions under real deadline constraints.<\/p><br \/><p>Qualifications:<\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>3+ years of development experience in object oriented programming using languages such as C# or Java<\/li><br \/><li>Strong knowledge of OOP and REST design principles<\/li><br \/><li>1+ years of relational database experience including schema design and SQL<\/li><br \/><li>Experience writing and maintaining a comprehensive suite of unit and integration tests<\/li><br \/><li>Ability to grow other engineers through code-reviews, design-reviews and over the shoulder debugging<\/li><br \/><li>Demonstrated experience working with a team to deliver software<\/li><br \/><li>Possess the passion to design, build and polish innovative applications<\/li><br \/><li>Experience writing distributed systems in a Cloud Computing environment such as AWS strongly preferred<\/li><br \/><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a technical major preferred<\/li><br \/><\/ul>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66719"},{"slug":"66712-remote-vb-net-developer-objectwise-consulting-group","id":"66712","epoch":"1524749680","date":"2018-04-26T06:34:40-07:00","company":"Objectwise Consulting Group","position":"VB.net Developer","tags":["dev","digital nomad"],"logo":"","description":"<p>We have been asked by a tier 1 IT consulting firm to help them staff a major initiative they they have beginning in May. As such we are looking for several&nbsp;developers with varying skills sets including VB.Net, C++, Perl, and even Cobol.&nbsp;Candidates must have outstanding communication&nbsp;skills and be client focused. Prior experience in banking is a plus.&nbsp;Expected duration is ~ 13&nbsp;months and could conceivably go longer.&nbsp;If you&nbsp;are coming available and interested please contact me by replying to this email with your availability date and hourly rate.<\/p>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66712"},{"slug":"66715-remote-azure-senior-consultant-codit","id":"66715","epoch":"1524749301","date":"2018-04-26T06:28:21-07:00","company":"Codit","position":"Azure Senior Consultant","tags":["consulting","senior"],"logo":"","description":"<p><strong>Job Description<\/strong><\/p><br \/><p>As an Azure Senior Consultant, you will be part of an international project team that works on cloud-based projects. You will mostly work at the customer location. Your primary responsibilities and duties within the team include:<\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Hands-on development, where we expect you to code along with the rest of the team. We are not looking for PowerPoint professionals: we are looking for individuals that can articulate their recommendations with authority and can develop them into a functional implementation.<\/li><br \/><li>Provide architectural guidance to the customer in the selection of the appropriate cloud services for the given use case.<\/li><br \/><li>Provide technical guidance to the more junior Codit team members that are working in your project.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p>If you have experience with the following topics, we would certainly love to have a chat with you and see how you can help us strengthen our team in Switzerland:<\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Designing and building secure RESTful Web APIs<\/li><br \/><li>Understanding of messaging patterns for distributed processing<\/li><br \/><li>Designing your software code to be decoupled and modular<\/li><br \/><li>Understanding of software patterns such as observables, decorator, singletons, factories, etc, and deciding for the correct pattern to apply to a specific problem<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong>Nice to know:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Due to Codit\'s strong collaboration with multiple Microsoft engineering teams, you will be working on the leading edge of technology, including private previews of products and services that are coming up in the company\'s roadmap.<\/li><br \/><li>You are never alone: you will find out how easily you can interact with other technology adepts throughout the world.<\/li><br \/><li>You will be leveraging Codit\'s competence centers and experts, which will help you e.g. with technical documentation templates, peer-reviewing your proposed solutions and code, among other things.<\/li><br \/><li>Codit has multiple Microsoft MVPs (Most Valuable Professionals). There will always be a colleague with deep technical knowledge of a topic where you might need some assistance or validation.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66715"},{"slug":"66713-remote-net-azure-architect-codit","id":"66713","epoch":"1524748762","date":"2018-04-26T06:19:22-07:00","company":"Codit","position":".Net Azure Architect","tags":["architecture"],"logo":"","description":"<p>The Architect within Codit is responsible for the technical quality that Codit delivers to customers.&nbsp; You will motivate your team members to obtain the required skill set to help Codit deliver the quality customers expect, and beyond.<\/p><br \/><p><strong>Skills &amp; Requirements<\/strong><\/p><br \/><p><strong><strong>About you: your profile<\/strong><\/strong><\/p><br \/><p>An experienced Architect with minimum&nbsp;5 years of IT experience, of which&nbsp;3 years dedicated to integration and SOA solutions. You should have, or be capable to adapt, a deep knowledge on BizTalk Server in all its aspects (Orchestration, BRE, Database Design, etc...) and Azure. Experience with B2B and SOA solutions is a must. You should be able to communicate in Dutch, English and French.<\/p><br \/><p><strong><strong>The basics of your job<\/strong><\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>As an Architect, you are involved in every single step of a project. This is what makes the job so interesting and challenging, using technologies such as XML, XSLT, XSD, .NET Framework, C#, Web Services, WCF, BizTalk Server, AppFabric, Azure and WABS.&nbsp;<\/li><br \/><li>You will get involved in the technical pre-sales. You convince customers with an excellent RFP\/RFI answer, a splendid proof of concept or a stunning demo presentation. You\'re also responsible for a high level project analysis and estimation.&nbsp;<\/li><br \/><li>At project kick-off, you design the solution architecture. Once this is in place, it\'s time to start with a detailed analysis. You gather all functional requirements which should result into a robust technical analysis. This involves a lot of meetings and discussions with the customer, so proper communication skills are a must.&nbsp;<\/li><br \/><li>It\'s your challenge to get your development team up to speed. You have a coaching role to make sure you get the maximum out of your team. A close follow-up is required in order to deliver quality and escalate problems in an early stage.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong><strong>That little extra to your daily job<\/strong><\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>You are never alone: you will find out how easily you can interact with other technology adepts throughout the world. And of course you are supported by the entire Codit integration competence center.<\/li><br \/><li>As a consultant, you get to work at our customers\' sites in Belgium.<\/li><br \/><li>A lot of our customers are international organizations, so you often work within an international context.<\/li><br \/><li>Because integration is directly connected to the core activity of the customer, you get acquainted with a lot of other business industries.<\/li><br \/><li>You can work with the newest Microsoft technologies, including the newest cloud solutions.<\/li><br \/><li>You work with people, not computers. You will coach other people, within Codit and\/or at the customer.<\/li><br \/><\/ul>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66713"},{"slug":"66708-remote-data-architect-otto","id":"66708","epoch":"1524741837","date":"2018-04-26T04:23:57-07:00","company":"Otto","position":"Data Architect","tags":["architecture"],"logo":"","description":"<p>Das bringt der Job:<\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Wir wollen die Nutzbarkeit und den Impact unserer Datenplattform f&uuml;r real-time- und batch-Verarbeitung im Konzern ma&szlig;geblich steigern &ndash; mit deiner Expertise!.<\/li><br \/><li>Gemeinsam mit Deinen Kollegen &uuml;bernimmst Du die Verantwortung f&uuml;r Konzeption und Umsetzung unserer neuen, hoch performanten und robusten Datenplattform in der Cloud f&uuml;r big, fast &amp; smart Data.<\/li><br \/><li>Du verantwortest die Verarbeitung und Aufbereitung der Daten entlang ihres gesamten Lebenszyklus in unseren Data Pipelines der Datenstromverarbeitung.<\/li><br \/><li>Du arbeitest mit unterschiedlichsten Datasets und stellst eine hohe Konsistenz sowie Verf&uuml;gbarkeit sicher und schaffst neue Einblicke zu unseren Kunden.<\/li><br \/><li>Du arbeitest mit unserem Data Science Kollegen im Team, um die (Daten-) Basis f&uuml;r neuartige Gesch&auml;fts- und Vorhersagemodelle bereitzustellen.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p>Das brauchen wir:<\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Gro&szlig;e Datenmengen, deren performante Verarbeitung sowie technische Innovationen sind Deine Leidenschaft.<\/li><br \/><li>Du besitzt hervorragende konzeptionelle F&auml;higkeiten, eine schnelle Auffassungsgabe und hast viel Freude an der Arbeit im Team.<\/li><br \/><li>Du hast fundierte Kenntnisse in der Verarbeitung gro&szlig;er, heterogener Datenmengen mit verteilten Systemen wie z.B. Hadoop, einen sicheren Umgang mit relationalen Datenbanken sowie mindestens erste Kenntnisse mit Real-Time-Ans&auml;tzen.<\/li><br \/><li>Dar&uuml;ber hinaus verf&uuml;gst du &uuml;ber erste Erfahrungen in der Entwicklung von skalierbaren Cloud-L&ouml;sungen auf Basis von AWS oder Google (z.B. Google Pub\/Sub, Google Dataflow, o.&auml;).<\/li><br \/><li>Starke und bew&auml;hrte Entwickler-Skills, bevorzugt in Java\/Scala\/Python und SQL sind f&uuml;r dich selbstverst&auml;ndlich.<\/li><br \/><li>Auf dein methodisches Vorgehen k&ouml;nnen wir uns verlassen: ein sauberes objekt-orientiertes oder funktionales Design, Tests und Monitorbarkeit zeichnet deine Software aus. Saubere Build- und Deploy-Prozesse sind Dir wichtig.<\/li><br \/><\/ul>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66708"},{"slug":"66707-remote-front-end-developer-marketing-site-screencloud","id":"66707","epoch":"1524734821","date":"2018-04-26T02:27:01-07:00","company":"ScreenCloud","position":"Front End Developer - Marketing site","tags":["front end","next.js","prismic cms","javascript","design","dev","marketing","digital nomad"],"logo":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/assets\/jobs\/239344389d367ac3d1b2e98a2025c631.png","description":"Front End Developer - Marketing site - Next.js, Prismic CMS\n\nScreenCloud makes it super simple for a business to turn any screen into a digital sign using consumer hardware. We have over 3,000 customers all over the world in retail & hospitality, education and corporate communications. They range from small businesses to huge enterprises. We have recently ramped up our marketing and need an experienced front end developer to support the team.\n\nWe are looking for a bright, enthusiastic and passionate person to manage the development of our marketing efforts. To begin with you will take on our new website and make it your own.\n\nWe are developing with next.js (https:\/\/github.com\/zeit\/next.js\/) with server rendering only of course. Right now we push to zeit now for easy deployment and then hook our dns to that.  The codebase utilises SCSS modules as well (https:\/\/github.com\/zeit\/next-plugins\/blob\/master\/packages\/next-sass\/readme.md)\n\nThe site hooks up to Prismic CMS https:\/\/prismic.io\/ up to this, the CMS structure for that is already in place. Prismic has a React lib https:\/\/prismic.io\/docs\/reactjs\/getting-started\/getting-started-from-scratch and https:\/\/github.com\/prismicio\/prismic-reactjs\n\nYou will have strong JavaScript and Front End engineering skills, be a strong team player and communicator with plenty of interest in technology and being part of a growing SaaS businesses.\n\nYou will be working with the design, content and marketing team to produce a world class top of funnel marketing platform.\n\nYou may question whether this is a full time role but we have plenty of initiatives we want to launch with resellers, partners, online education, developer sites etc. There will be plenty of work!\n\nREQUIREMENTS\n\nWe are looking for someone with experience of working in an online agency or business (preferably SaaS). You will need to be a self-starter and creative in your thinking around potential opportunities we could seize to help us grow our business.\n\nSpecifically we would be looking for:\n\nAt least 3 years experience in a front end developer role\nStrong attention to detail\nDesign orientated\nUp to speed on technical SEO requirements\nThoughtful about page speed optimisation\nProven creative problem-solving\nMotivated and able to work autonomously\nInterest in technology and SaaS-businesses\n\nBENEFITS\nCompetitive salary based on experience and qualifications. We also have an employee share scheme that you would be eligible for after 3 months.\n\nIn terms of holiday we have an unlimited policy. This is because we want to treat people like adults and not track every bit of time off they have.\n\nWe are open to remote workers or those that want to base with our London office. Our preference is for those within a 3 hour time zone radius of the UK for closer collaboration. We will organise two company offsite trips per year so you will feel a proper part of the team. We are an international company with teams in UK, USA, Ukraine and Thailand. We look forward to hearing from you!\n\nKEY TECH SKILLS\n\nJavascript\nFrontend Development\nSCSS \/ SASS\nReact.js\nNext.Js\nPrismic CMS","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66707"},{"slug":"66704-remote-mobile-developer-vox-markets","id":"66704","epoch":"1524728370","date":"2018-04-26T00:39:30-07:00","company":"Vox Markets","position":"Mobile Developer","tags":["mobile","ios","android","react native","javascript","react","dev","digital nomad","ios"],"logo":"","description":"<p>We are looking for a talented Mobile developer to join our team asap.<\/p><br \/><p>You will cooperate&nbsp;<strong>remotely<\/strong>&nbsp; with our team of developers from the UK, Poland, Russia and Ukraine and will be directly in touch with our lead developer in London&nbsp; to lead and deliver projects in a timely fashion.<\/p><br \/><p>It is a new role within the company.<\/p><br \/><br \/><p>We are looking for someone who is great under pressure, have experience of working in distributed teams, can think outside the box and isn&rsquo;t constrained by traditional approaches to solving complex issues.<\/p><br \/><p>The successful candidate would have skills in:<\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>iOS and\/or Android<\/li><br \/><li>React Native (or just React.js with a willingness to learn React Native)<\/li><br \/><li>Consuming data from RESTful WebServices<\/li><br \/><li>A working knowledge of microservice architecture also desirable but not essential.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p>The work will be mobile heavy but with occasional web tasks.<\/p>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66704"},{"slug":"66703-remote-launchpad-launchpad","id":"66703","epoch":"1524727148","date":"2018-04-26T00:19:08-07:00","company":"LaunchPad","position":"Full Stack Developer","tags":["full stack","developer","dev","digital nomad"],"logo":"","description":"<p>We are looking for an experienced Full-stack developer from Ukraine to join our team asap. It is a remote role.<\/p><br \/><p><strong>Essential Skills:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Substantial experience of web development in Ruby on Rails<\/li><br \/><li>Experience with ReactJS and relevant libraries (Redux)<\/li><br \/><li>Experience in JavaScript, jQuery, HTML5, HTML and CSS<\/li><br \/><li>Experience in manipulating data, REST API, and Json<\/li><br \/><li>Experience using relational databases such as MySQL.<\/li><br \/><li>The ability to approach code refactoring and architecture in a highly strategic manner<\/li><br \/><li>Good communication, have an analytic mindset, and be a fast learner<\/li><br \/><li>Experience in startup environments and agile-like development<\/li><br \/><li>The ability to effectively manage your own work<\/li><br \/><li>Computer Science degree or equivalent<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong>Nice To Have:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Experience with building and maintaining production systems on AWS<\/li><br \/><li>Experience with continuous integration, testing, and deployment<\/li><br \/><li>Web application security<\/li><br \/><li>Knowledge of Video technology<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong>Benefits:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>A great working environment<\/li><br \/><li>Supportive team and the opportunity to work with a fast moving, relaxed and energetic business<\/li><br \/><li>Yearly get together of the whole development and product team in the Philippines<\/li><br \/><\/ul>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66703"},{"slug":"66697-remote-technical-product-marketing-manager-auth0","id":"66697","epoch":"1524685307","date":"2018-04-25T12:41:47-07:00","company":"Auth0","position":"Technical Product Marketing Manager","tags":["product manager","exec","marketing"],"logo":"","description":"Auth0 is a fast-growing identity-as-a-service company headquartered in Seattle, Washington, with a distributed global team located in over thirty countries. Thousands of enterprises around the world use the Auth0 platform to implement authentication, authorization and related security functionality to speed their time to market, reduce their costs, and improve their security.<br \/><br \/>Auth0 is loved by developers and trusted by global enterprises. More than 500.000 unique users visit <a href=\"http:\/\/auth0.com\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Auth0.com<\/a> each month due to our compelling content and the functionality of our identity platform. Our mission is to simplify developers&rsquo; lives, improve security, and reduce identity TCO for our enterprise customers, by making identity simple, secure and extensible. We strive to maintain a welcoming and inclusive <a href=\"https:\/\/auth0.com\/blog\/our-culture-and-values-at-auth0\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">culture<\/a> built on the principle of &ldquo;No B.A.P.&rdquo; (No BS, No A-holes, No Politics).<br \/><br \/>We are recruiting an entrepreneurial, creative and analytical technical product marketer to help us aggressively drive our go-to-market efforts. &nbsp;Auth0&rsquo;s offering is a platform that can address nearly every identity security scenario, so we need a highly innovative individual to help us expand our reach further into the enterprise space. &nbsp;Reporting to the Director, Product Marketing, &nbsp;you will be an integral part of the team that creates the plan, strategies and tactics to further build Auth0&rsquo;s market leadership position.<br \/><br \/><strong>Responsibilities:<\/strong><br \/><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Perform in-depth technical analysis of competitor features\/products to determine optimal competitive positioning; become the go-to expert for all items related to the market trends and competitive landscape.<\/li><br \/><li>Be willing to get &ldquo;hands-on&rdquo; with the product and deliver well thought-through analysis on product and competitive positioning.<\/li><br \/><li>Maintain a broad and deep technical understanding of the Auth0 product line and the underlying technologies and protocols.<\/li><br \/><li>Create high-impact sales enablement tools and technical marketing content including collateral, demos, whitepapers, sales scripts and presentations.<\/li><br \/><li>Collaborate with pre-sales team and assist in building powerful product demos to support sales engagements during customer meetings and marketing events.<\/li><br \/><li>Develop GTM plans and collaborate with product management and other cross-functional teams to launch new products and features.<\/li><br \/><li>Ability to translate complex technical concepts and technologies into business-oriented and customer-centric value propositions.<\/li><br \/><li>Build deep product expertise and clearly articulate on technical and competitive topics to internal and external audiences, including engineering teams, product teams and industry analysts.<\/li><br \/><li>Develop a solid understanding of use cases for consumer, employees, partner and IoT IAM.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong>Qualifications:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Experience with programming languages and application development that will enable you to be &ldquo;hands-on&rdquo; with the product.<\/li><br \/><li>3+ years in technical marketing, evangelism, pre-sales engineering or product development\/management roles.<\/li><br \/><li>Experience delivering technical sales enablement to software sales organizations.<\/li><br \/><li>Prior experience in identity and security technologies, APIs and web services preferred.<\/li><br \/><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s in computer science, engineering or related experience.<\/li><br \/><li>Prior experience in identity and security technologies, APIs and web services preferred.<\/li><br \/><li>Excellent interpersonal, project management, and communication skills.<\/li><br \/><li>Strong presentation skills and the ability to communicate effectively with senior management and key customers.<\/li><br \/><li>Strong attention to detail and ability to juggle several projects at the same time.<\/li><br \/><li>Be an amazing team player and be willing to go above and beyond to win as a team.<\/li><br \/><li>Must be able to take initiative, follow-up and drive cross-departmental actions in order to meet challenging deadlines.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong>Location:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Bellevue WA, Buenos Aires AR, or remote.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p>Auth0 is an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. Auth0 conducts all employment-related activities without regard to race, religion, color, national origin, age, sex, marital status, sexual orientation, disability, citizenship status, genetics, or status as a Vietnam-era special disabled and other covered veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law. Auth0 participates in E-Verify and will provide the federal government with your Form I-9 information to confirm that you are authorized to work in the U.S.<\/p>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66697"},{"slug":"66696-remote-devops-engineer-blockstack","id":"66696","epoch":"1524679543","date":"2018-04-25T11:05:43-07:00","company":"Blockstack","position":"DevOps Engineer","tags":["devops","sre","python","javascript","linux","aws","cloud","monitoring","testing","security","infosec","engineer","devops"],"logo":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/assets\/jobs\/aad370cf00affdcdcecc5861957cd2fe.png","description":"Blockstack is a new internet for decentralized apps. With Blockstack, you own your data and maintain your privacy, security and freedom. Blockstack is open source project and a public benefit corporation. [Learn more](https:\/\/blockstack.org).\n\nBlockstack is looking for a passionate and collaborative DevOps Engineer to help develop rigorous testing suites to guarantee the safety of a soon-to-be launched cryptocurrency and blockchain. This person will work on implementing securely tested solutions, and interface with our dev team and back end engineers on product builds and feature implementation. This role will span testing and security, software development and upgrades, improvements to our Developer API, and community support.  \n\nOur engineering team builds software using JavaScript\/ES6, React, Redux, Swift, and Objective-C on the frontend and Python, bash, and Bitcoin Core on the backend.\n\nThings You\'ll Work On:\n- Manage distribution of Blockstack software upgrades for developers and everyday users\n- Keep our users happy by managing Blockstack browser availability, scalability, and performance \n- Build tools for faster deployment schedules \n- Instate monitoring protocols and fail-over measures \n- Implement continuous testing practices to ensure the security and performance  goals of Blockstack are met across backend services, blockchain infrastructure, and our frontend user clients\n- Deliver on rapid implementation schedules (without compromising on smart development goals and principles) to build web functionality that is functional, fast, and scalable\n\nQualifications\nYou are have worked in a large, highly available systems environment before, as well as an agile start-up. You are familiar with strategizing and improving for system security and availability. Your strengths lie in backend development, but can work across the full-stack when needed.  \n\nKPIs\n- Increased uptime of Blockstack software \n- Delivery of long term, securely tested software \n- Work to improve our failure processes, alerting, and emergency response times \n- Support our community developers to increase number and usability of Blockstack Apps \n\nSkills \n- Experience developing with python and bash\n- Comfort across operating systems, with a strong Linux background\n- Experience across the CI\/CD pipeline, with an understanding of best practices for automated testing and deployment\n- Ability to build and maintain highly available infrastructure\n- Competency in monitoring and quick response time in the event of an emergency\n- Security background with strength in automated testing and infrastructure\n- Experience deploying Bitcoin infrastructure with bitcoin core or utxo providers\n\nQualities + Traits \n- Passion for building the new internet for decentralized apps  \n- Strong problem solving skills, ability to think fast and thoroughly\n- Development mindset with strong security background\n- Experience in a rapidly scaling start-up\n- Proactive solution provider\n- Excellent communication","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66696"},{"slug":"66692-remote-documentation-engineer-blockstack","id":"66692","epoch":"1524665991","date":"2018-04-25T07:19:51-07:00","company":"Blockstack","position":"Documentation Engineer","tags":["javascript","technical writer","documentation","blockchain","developer evangelism","dev","engineer","digital nomad"],"logo":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/assets\/jobs\/c3e3215056dbe7e5c858696813866d5f.png","description":"Blockstack is a new internet for decentralized apps. With Blockstack, you own your data and maintain your privacy, security and freedom. Blockstack is open source project and a public benefit corporation. [Learn more](https:\/\/blockstack.org\/).\n\nBlockstack is looking for experienced engineers with excellent communication and writing skills to improve our developer and API documentation. This role is crucial for increasing Blockstack accessibility and building user engagement in the Blockstack community. This person will convey complex concepts and UI instructions to a developer audience and engage with the engineering and product teams to deliver succinct product writing updates at a rapid rate. \n\nThings you\'ll work on:\n- Create  developer instructions during Blockstack feature upgrades, improvements, and architectural builds \n- Improve organization and copy of existing developer tool instructions internally and externally across the Blockstack website, github, and forum\n- Communicate with and support a global developer audience \n- User test copy and make evidence based improvements \n- Create sample apps and code snippets for demonstration  \n\nQualifications:\n- You have built an fully functioning, polished app \n- 5+ years professional development experience\n\nSkills:\n- Experience with technical writing and communications, and have written for a global audience \n- Experience with JavaScript\/ES6, React, Redux, and Swift\n- Experience working for a rapidly scaling start-up \n- Passion for delivering high-quality work, with quick turnaround times\n\nQualities & Traits:\n- Passion for building the new internet for decentralized apps  \n- Strong problem solving skills, ability to think fast and thoroughly \n- Proactive solution provider \n- Excellent communication\n\nWe get a lot of applicants, and have historically hired people who are proactively involved in our work and mission of decentralizing the internet. We hope you explore our [Whitepaper](https:\/\/blockstack.org\/whitepaper.pdf), [Browser](https:\/\/blockstack.org\/install), [Github](https:\/\/github.com\/blockstack), and [Slack](https:\/\/docs.google.com\/a\/blockstack.com\/forms\/d\/e\/1FAIpQLSed5Mnu0G5ZMJdWs6cTO_8sTJfUVfe1sYL6WFDcD51_XuQkZw\/viewform) prior to submitting your resume.","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66692"},{"slug":"66714-remote-community-of-volunteers-creating-a-map-helping-people-who-are-homeless-around-the-world-focallocal-the-public-happiness-movement","id":"66714","epoch":"1524657915","date":"2018-04-25T05:05:15-07:00","company":"Focallocal - The Public Happiness Movement","position":"Community of Volunteers creating a map helping people who are homeless around the world","tags":["meteor js","javascript","meteor js"],"logo":"","description":"","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66714"},{"slug":"66683-remote-marketing-seo-intern-paid-skyrocket-digital","id":"66683","epoch":"1524642586","date":"2018-04-25T00:49:46-07:00","company":"Skyrocket Digital","position":"Marketing & SEO \/\/ Intern (Paid)","tags":["online marketing","seo","marketing","non tech"],"logo":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/assets\/jobs\/a697a2620ba6245ecb0d65447a7d2259.png","description":"We are currently looking to hire a Digital Marketing \/ SEO intern to join a distributed marketing team that grows our platform DOYOUYOGA.COM. This is a paid position.\nIf everything goes well, we\'ll offer you to join the team as a full time remote employee (Marketing Manager).\n*Heads up: SEO experience required*\n# About DOYOUYOGA & Skyrocket\nWe\'re a young and rapidly growing digital media company serving millions of lifestyle\u00c2\u00ad conscious consumers worldwide. We\u00e2\u0080\u0099re building a kickass platform, publishing meaningful content that changes people\u00e2\u0080\u0099s lives. Founded in 2012, DOYOUYOGA is now one of the largest and fastest growing yoga and lifestyle platforms on the web. Growing from zero to a combined reach of over 5 million monthly users in less than three years, we\u00e2\u0080\u0099re taking things to the next level\u00e2\u0080\u00a6and so can you.\n# About the job\nWe\'re looking for a highly motivated, creative, and organized intern to join the Marketing team (minimum 3 months). Your heart beats digital and you have a proven experience with online marketing? Then this might be your chance to join a great team of doers, and entrepreneurial minds. Here is what you will do:\n\n*Team Work*\n\n- Collaborate and communicate with your team and have fun doing it;\n- Work on meaningful projects and assignments with tangible, real-world results.\n- Get incredibly valuable insights into a rapidly growing web platform with millions of users.\n\n*Search Engine Optimization*\n\n- Run your own (white hat) SEO projects on DOYOUYOGA (onsite and offsite);\n- Research of relevant SEO topics and creation of content for our target group;\n- Perform keyword analysis, planning, and optimization;\n- Increase traffic through SEO.\n\n*Digital Marketing*\n\n- Gain insights into content marketing, email marketing, and most fields of digital marketing in general\n\n*Your skills*\n\n- It doesn\u00e2\u0080\u0099t matter if or what you studied. We want a bright and open mind;\n- Great English skills are important.\n- Experience with Google Analytics;\n- You\u00e2\u0080\u0099re proactive and have a positive \u00e2\u0080\u009ccan do\u00e2\u0080\u009d attitude;\n- You\u00e2\u0080\u0099re organized, self-motivated, detail-oriented and able to work independently.\n- We\'re NOT looking for a yoga or fitness expert. No yoga knowledge required. This is a marketing role! \n\nAre you ready to take responsibility and grow your skills on all levels? We\u00e2\u0080\u0099d love to hear from you!\n\nTell us why you\u00e2\u0080\u0099re perfect for this job! Send your application including resume and cover letter to jobs (a) skyrocket (dot) cc","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66683"},{"slug":"66679-remote-software-engineer-urbandoor","id":"66679","epoch":"1524629831","date":"2018-04-24T21:17:11-07:00","company":"Urbandoor","position":"Software Engineer","tags":["dev","engineer","digital nomad"],"logo":"","description":"Full Time: Sr. Software Engineer (Ruby\/Rails) at Urbandoor in San Francisco, CA or Remote","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66679"},{"slug":"66678-remote-c-web-application-developer-fbs","id":"66678","epoch":"1524605625","date":"2018-04-24T14:33:45-07:00","company":"FBS","position":"C# Web Application Developer","tags":["dev","web dev","c plus plus","digital nomad","c","c","c plus plus"],"logo":"","description":"<p>Are you passionate about web applications and real estate and want to combine them in your career? &nbsp; FBS is looking for&nbsp;a C# web developer to join our new Spring&nbsp;development team. We lead real estate software innovation with our web application&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/flexmls.com\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Flexmls<\/a>&nbsp;and are a profitable, 100% employee owned company, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.flexmls.com\/about\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">celebrating 40&nbsp;years<\/a>&nbsp;in the real estate industry.&nbsp; <a href=\"http:\/\/geekestateblog.com\/fbs-acquires-solid-earths-spring-software-platform\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">FBS&nbsp;recently acquired Spring<\/a>, which&nbsp;helps real estate MLSs, brokers, and agents with tools to grow their businesses and for consumers to search for homes.&nbsp;You\'d be building features and improving existing features for our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.flexmls.com\/products\/spring-mls-portal\/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Spring&nbsp;system<\/a>, which serves real estate multiple listing services, brokers, and agents across the country, including their home buyer and seller clients.<\/p><br \/><p><strong>Skills &amp; Requirements<\/strong><\/p><br \/><p>C#, HTML, CSS, Node.js, JavaScript, jQuery, MongoDB, Git, and passion for web development and delighting customers by continually improving the customer experience. &nbsp;Ability to consider the impacts of new and changed code on the entire system in addition to the current piece of code is essential, with an eye towards creating sustainable systems for the long run.&nbsp; Experience with relational and non-relational databases and use of APIs as data storage is useful as well.&nbsp; Excellent communication skills are important, as you\'ll often be working with remote teammates.&nbsp; This position can be either remote or in FBS\'s office in Fargo, ND.<\/p>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66678"},{"slug":"66676-remote-full-stack-developer-openlaw-a-consensys-spoke","id":"66676","epoch":"1524603627","date":"2018-04-24T14:00:27-07:00","company":"OpenLaw a ConsenSys Spoke","position":"Full Stack Developer","tags":["full stack","dev","digital nomad"],"logo":"","description":"<p><span>OpenLaw is a ConsenSys spoke that has built the first &ldquo;smart&rdquo; legal agreements. We&rsquo;re using blockchain technology to reimagine the future of commerce and the $160 billion transactional legal market.<\/span><span><br><\/span><\/p><br \/><p><strong>About Us: <\/strong><\/p><br \/><p><span>At its core, OpenLaw is a multi-module blockchain-based protocol and markup language to prepare, manage, and execute smart legal agreements. Using the OpenLaw protocol you can seamlessly execute a range of commercial transactions, store digital signatures on a blockchain, and execute smart contracts.<\/span><\/p><br \/><p>We use Scala as our main programming language along with JavaScript React for our frontend. Our backend uses LevelDB, and Ethereum to store, search, and verify data. We are product driven and committed to open source. That means our end goal is to the deliver the best and fastest product possible for our users and to do so in a community driven manner.<\/p><br \/><p>OpenLaw is a remote-first organization with team members distributed across the globe, and we are committed to building both our team and our software in a thoughtful, inclusive, and sustainable fashion.<\/p><br \/><p>We are currently looking for experienced full-stack engineers to join our team. This is a role for engineers who can collaborate with a team to architect and deliver feature upgrades and improvements. Engineering partners in this role have built features such as custom integrations and have implemented significant changes to the application architecture. You should be comfortable working in diverse development ecosystems and collaboratively within a rapidly growing team.<\/p><br \/><p><strong>Responsibilities:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li><span>Implement OpenLaw feature upgrades, improvements, and architectural builds <\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>Collaborate with the team to ship major product builds <\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>Provide thoughtful implementation estimates and &nbsp;build functionality that is fast, scalable, and upholds sustainable development goals and principles<\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>Keep our users happy by maintaining the software, troubleshooting and fixing bugs.<\/span><\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong>Desired Skills:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li><span>5+ years professional development experience<\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>Experience working within a remote-first and globally distributed team <\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>Experience in API Design (REST or other).<\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>Strong familiarity with functional programming methodologies<\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>Familiar with front-end languages like JavaScript with toolkits like React<\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>Comfortable working on multiple codebases, with the ability to quickly understand new projects and tooling systems<\/span><\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong>Bonus:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li><span>Previous development experience using Scala, Akka, <\/span><span>CQRS or Domain Driven Design<\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>High-level understanding of public-private key encryption protocols<\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>Experience with cloud infrastructure (e.g. AWS, Azure)<\/span><\/li><br \/><li><span>An active interest or involvement with the broader open source community<\/span><\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p>At OpenLaw you must balance passion for the technology while knowing when and how to focus the conversation on our users. At OpenLaw we enjoy an open and inclusive culture, the freedom to explore and experiment. We are continuously iterating together on improving our work methodology and team culture.<\/p><br \/><p><span>If you are someone that thrives in a rapidly-evolving environment while being self-directed, detail-oriented, communicative, and adaptable, we would love to hear from you. &nbsp;Please feel free to join our <\/span><a href=\"http:\/\/openlawteam.slack.com\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span>Slack<\/span><\/a><span> or check out our <\/span><span><a href=\"https:\/\/medium.com\/@OpenLaw1\" rel=\"nofollow\">Medium<\/a>&nbsp;<\/span><span>page before applying.<\/span><\/p>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66676"},{"slug":"66677-remote-product-manager-openlaw-a-consensys-spoke","id":"66677","epoch":"1524603422","date":"2018-04-24T13:57:02-07:00","company":"OpenLaw a ConsenSys Spoke","position":"Product Manager","tags":["product manager","exec"],"logo":"","description":"<p>OpenLaw is a ConsenSys spoke that has built the first &ldquo;smart&rdquo; legal agreements. We&rsquo;re using blockchain technology to reimagine the future of commerce and the $160 billion transactional legal market.<\/p><br \/><p><strong>About Us: <\/strong><\/p><br \/><p>At its core, OpenLaw is a multi-module blockchain-based protocol and markup language to prepare, manage, and execute smart legal agreements. Using the OpenLaw protocol you can seamlessly execute a range of commercial transactions, store digital signatures on a blockchain, and execute smart contracts.<\/p><br \/><p>OpenLaw is a remote-first organization with team members distributed across the globe, and we are committed to building both our team and our software in a thoughtful, inclusive, and sustainable fashion.<\/p><br \/><p>OpenLaw is looking for a Product Manager to join our team. This role will be focused on improving design, user experience, and usability of our browser-based web application. This position is ideal for experienced product managers who have built a product from the ground up, who have a proven ability to build and grow a user base, and can establish practices to improve user experience. This role will interface across teams and be incorporated across feedback loops. Therefore, successful candidates must be highly research driven and communicative.<\/p><br \/><p><strong>Responsibilities:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Be the &ldquo;voice of the user&rdquo; in understanding, analyzing, and advocating for considered feature tradeoffs<\/li><br \/><li>Improve the experience for and increasing the usability of the OpenLaw application<\/li><br \/><li>Propose, manage, and measure KPIs for the quality and growth of the OpenLaw application and open source contributor ecosystem<\/li><br \/><li>Project management to effectively deliver on rapid iterative development cycles without compromising quality or engineering principles.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong>Desired Skills:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Experience in Product Management within an asynchronous project development process on a fully remote and globally distributed team<\/li><br \/><li>Obsessive about excellent UX and strong experience working with wireframes, user stories, et al.<\/li><br \/><li>Track record of owning and driving growth on a polished client-facing technical product<\/li><br \/><li>You have both strong technical and business acumen, and experience turning growth principles into engineering deliverables<\/li><br \/><li>4-7 years of professional work experience<\/li><br \/><li>Excel at project management, organization and communication<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p>At OpenLaw you must balance passion for the technology while knowing when and how to focus the conversation on our users. At OpenLaw we enjoy an open and inclusive culture, competitive benefits, and the freedom to explore and experiment. We are continuously iterating together on improving our work methodology and team culture.<\/p><br \/><p>If you are someone that thrives in a rapidly-evolving environment while being self-directed, detail-oriented, communicative, and adaptable, we would love to hear from you. &nbsp;Please feel free to join our <a href=\"http:\/\/openlawteam.slack.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Slack<\/a> or check out our <a href=\"https:\/\/medium.com\/@OpenLaw1\" rel=\"nofollow\">Medium<\/a>&nbsp;page before applying.<\/p>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66677"},{"slug":"66674-remote-machine-learning-engineer-hays-specialist-recruitment","id":"66674","epoch":"1524592810","date":"2018-04-24T11:00:10-07:00","company":"Hays Specialist Recruitment","position":"Machine Learning Engineer","tags":["machine learning","engineer"],"logo":"","description":"<br><br>Machine Learning Engineer opportunity in Belfast - Diaceutics are a PharamaTech data organisation. <br><br><br><strong>Your new company<\/strong> <br> Diaceutics are a brand new entrant to the Northern Ireland market - a Medtech organisation that have been in business for almost 15 years and count some of the leading organisations within the health\/pharmacy world as their clients. This role is a strategic appointment as the company seeks to deliver their customers a true competitive advantage by appointing N.I.\'s best data talent within it\'s ranks to develop outstanding products and solutions. <br> <br> <strong>Your new role<\/strong> <br> Directing the organisation\'s analytics capabilities, you\'ll have the opportunity to develop new solutions using cutting edge tools and algorithms. Your key responsibility will be to analyse current data sets and identify supportive data sets for NPD in a highly collaborative and driven product environment. You\'ll claim ownership for the design, development, delivery and evaluation of these new solutions and directly influence company strategic decision making with your expertise and knowledge. <br> <br> <strong>What you\'ll need to succeed<\/strong> <br> Ideally you should be educated to MSc or PhD level within an IT\/mathematical\/scientific discipline and have an intermediate level of experience. You\'ll be passionate about being hands on in developing algorithms\/mathematical models whilst also taking a step up to being involved at a more senior strategic level. Ideally, you should have skills within cloud-based systems, be comfortable in a programming language (Java\/Python\/C++) and have a high level of competency in data modelling\/manipulation. Your experience in Machine Learning, Neural Networks and Deep Learning are considerably attractive to your new organisation. <br> <br> <strong>What you\'ll get in return<\/strong> <br> This unique opportunity will provide you with a substantial salary and benefits package in line with your data science experience. As a Director, you\'ll be given the opportunity to directly influence the company direction and be positioned as the company ambassador for Data Science\/ML in lectures\/events etc. <br> <br> <strong>What you need to do now<\/strong><br> If you\'re interested in this role, click \'apply now\' to forward an up-to-date copy of your CV, or call Jason Brownlee at Hays IT now.<br> <br> If this job isn\'t quite right for you but you are looking for a new position, please contact us for a confidential discussion on your career.<br> <br> <strong>Hays Digital Technology is working exclusively in partnership with Diaceutics to manage the recruitment of this position. <br> <\/strong><br><br>Hays Specialist Recruitment Limited acts as an employment agency for permanent recruitment and employment business for the supply of temporary workers. By applying for this job you accept the T&amp;C\'s, Privacy Policy and Disclaimers which can be found at hays.co.uk","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66674"},{"slug":"66675-remote-frontend-ui-developer-britecore","id":"66675","epoch":"1524591574","date":"2018-04-24T10:39:34-07:00","company":"BriteCore","position":"Frontend UI Developer","tags":["design","dev","digital nomad"],"logo":"","description":"<p>We are hiring for a mid-level frontend developer who will be able to bridge the gap between our design and full stack development teams. The ideal person will have solid HTML, CSS and JS skills and be able to craft delightful user experiences in a scalable way.<br><br>This is a position on our design team, which means you will have a big say in how we architect the design system that powers all of our app\'s UI and UX. With that in mind, we are looking for someone who can do more than just re-create a mockup &ndash; We\'re looking for someone who can think critically and help us create better experiences for our users, while working closely with our full stack developers who are creating the core business logic.<br><br><strong>The kind of work we do<\/strong><br>BriteCore is essentially a CMS for insurance companies. They use it to manage all aspects of their business, including tracking policies, contacts and handling claims.<br><br>This means our users typically see our app more as a business tool like Microsoft Word or Google Sheets than a website (even though it is completely a web app). They also are using BriteCore for several hours every day, and are concerned with doing things quickly and efficiently. This, along with the complicated nature of insurance, means we deal with some complex workflows, and try to set ourselves apart from our competitors with a smooth UX that helps them navigate these tough processes.<br><br><strong>What you might be doing<\/strong><br>We\'re looking for someone who can really help us take our frontend system to the next level, and this includes things like:<\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Creating, in collaboration with designers, a modular, scalable design system that can be used by other developers to quickly and consistently build out new features.<\/li><br \/><li>Implementing a robust hotkey system, to allow our users to quickly accomplish tasks in the app.<\/li><br \/><li>Help us implement better user analytics, and eventually allow us to A\/B test new features\/designs.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><br><strong>What it is like to work here<\/strong><br>BriteCore is a remote-first company &mdash; even employees who live in our home city of Springfield, MO usually work from home! And most of the people you will work with are scattered across the US and the globe. This means that remote team members are just as much part of the company as local employees. We also allow a lot of flexibility in terms of time off. In return, we expect all of our employees to be productive and accountable, which means you\'ll work alongside a great, dedicated team.<br><br><strong>Responsibilities<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Work alongside designers to implement features, with a focus on great UX.&nbsp;<\/li><br \/><li>Have a keen sense for what makes an attractive UI<\/li><br \/><li>Structure and develop code in a component-driven, scalable way<\/li><br \/><li>Have a thorough understanding of HTML\/CSS\/JS best practices.<\/li><br \/><li>Communicate clearly<\/li><br \/><li>Welcome feedback and collaboration<\/li><br \/><li>Be friendly, confident, and patient with others<\/li><br \/><li>Self-direct<\/li><br \/><li>Stay up on industry best practices and trends<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><br><strong>Technologies We Use<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Vue.js (Experience with Vue, or another frontend JS framework is required)<\/li><br \/><li>SCSS<\/li><br \/><li>PostCSS<\/li><br \/><li>HTML5<\/li><br \/><li>Webpack<\/li><br \/><li>Github, various CLI tools<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><br><strong>Benefits and Compensation<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>$50k-$70k based on experience and proven performance<\/li><br \/><li>Benefit from working alongside and observing a team of world-class engineers and designers<\/li><br \/><li>Comprehensive health insurance coverage including medical, dental, and vision for US-based applicants<\/li><br \/><li>Flexible schedule<\/li><br \/><li>Relaxed work environment<\/li><br \/><li>Remote work<\/li><br \/><li>Flexible learning time &mdash; explore your ideas and new technologies on the clock<\/li><br \/><\/ul>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66675"},{"slug":"66672-remote-freelance-frontend-developer-forward-action","id":"66672","epoch":"1524589181","date":"2018-04-24T09:59:41-07:00","company":"Forward Action","position":"Freelance Frontend Developer","tags":["javascript","html","css","design","dev","digital nomad","css","html"],"logo":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/assets\/jobs\/d04bccb68d3225fea1fc62a2cd54cffb.png","description":"##Summary\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a Freelance front end developer to do 4 days of work over the first 2 weeks of June 2018. And after that, if everything goes well, we would like to add them to the group of freelancers that we regularly call on to work with.\r\n\r\nYou will be taking a design (probably in Zeplin.io) and turning it into a growth-focused microsite, an example of which is [here](http:\/\/weather.sumofus.org\/).\r\n\r\nWe\u00e2\u0080\u0099re a remote-working first organisation and are happy to hear from anyone within a time difference of 1 hour of London who is willing to work London hours. You will also have the option to work from our London office in Hoxton.\r\n\r\nTo apply for this role, please fill out the short application form here: [Application Form.](https:\/\/forwardaction.typeform.com\/to\/bVoAk8?source=remoteok) By 11:59 pm on 7th May 2018.\r\n\r\nShortlisted candidates will be asked to attend a short interview via a video call.\r\n\r\n## Who we are\r\n\r\nForward Action is a full service digital agency for progressive causes. We work with clients from campaign conception through to results, creating strategies, content and tools to get the job done.\r\n\r\nOur clients are some of the most exciting and impactful organisations in campaigning, including Greenpeace, The Labour Party, Amnesty International, WaterAid, and SumOfUs.\r\n\r\n## Full job advert\r\n\r\nThe full job advert is [here](http:\/\/forwardaction.uk\/jobs\/?source=remoteok).\r\n","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66672"},{"slug":"66669-remote-security-engineer-malwareanalyse-macos-vmray","id":"66669","epoch":"1524578948","date":"2018-04-24T07:09:08-07:00","company":"VMRay","position":"Security Engineer Malwareanalyse MacOS","tags":["macos","infosec","engineer","macos"],"logo":"","description":"<p><strong>SECURITY ENGINEER (M\/F)<\/strong><\/p><br \/><p><strong>Malware Analysis macOS<\/strong><\/p><br \/><p>Location:<\/p><br \/><p>Bochum, Germany<\/p><br \/><p><strong>Remote work:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><p>Partial<\/p><br \/><p><strong>Responsibilities:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><p>We are looking for a new Software Engineer focused on macOS. Your main task will be to research, design, and implement effective detection rules based on results from our static and dynamic analysis. You will be responsible for identifying typical malware behavior patterns by analyzing macOS malware and eventually turning your findings into detection rules. You will collaborate with the rest of the development team to provide insights that help improve the efficacy and performance of VMRay Analyzer. The job requires a strong interest in gaining an in-depth understanding of macOS internals, such as official and unofficial APIs, binary file formats, kernel internals, etc. You will have to keep yourself and the team up to date with the current macOS malware landscape.<\/p><br \/><p><strong>Requirements:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Strong interest in macOS internals and malware analysis<\/li><br \/><li>Good knowledge of macOS API<\/li><br \/><li>Proficient with Python programming or at least one similar high-level programming language<\/li><br \/><li>Experience in malware analysis is a plus<\/li><br \/><li>Fluent in English<\/li><br \/><li>On-site employment at our headquarters in Bochum (partial remote work possible)<\/li><br \/><\/ul>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66669"},{"slug":"66666-remote-senior-ios-developers-authority-partners","id":"66666","epoch":"1524573828","date":"2018-04-24T05:43:48-07:00","company":"Authority Partners","position":"Senior IOS Developers","tags":["ios","senior","ios"],"logo":"","description":"<