rate of 50-70% annually, so you&rsquo;ll want to get on board this fast-moving ship. Our distinct workflow solution, including Electronic Medical Record (EMR), Practice Management (PM), Managed IT services, and Billing Services is currently provided to thousands of clinics across the nation. We offer great benefits, and we&rsquo;re not averse to having fun on the job.<\/p><br \/><p><strong>Who We Need:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><p>We are seeking a Data Architect to support the&nbsp;applications and systems that deliver Saas Solutions in the Urgent Care Healthcare market. Our ideal candidate has a passion for learning new things and applying technology to solve complex software business solutions.<\/p><br \/><p><strong>What You&rsquo;ll Do:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Develop, validate, publish, and maintain logical and physical data models<\/li><br \/><li>Develop, document, and communicate data architectural guidelines and frameworks<\/li><br \/><li>Formulate and implement data governance procedures and policies<\/li><br \/><li>Review program\/project data architecture for compliance with IT standards, policies, regulations, and architectural plans.<\/li><br \/><li>Identify data architectural risks and propose alternatives, mitigations, and solutions<\/li><br \/><li>Assisting in the development of standards for the design and development of system databases<\/li><br \/><li>Support R&amp;D to deliver technology evaluations and recommendations for managing and integrating data<\/li><br \/><li>Provide data analysis and design in support of new enterprise services and system modernization efforts<\/li><br \/><li>Work with Analysts, Software developers, DBAs, and project teams and stakeholders to achieve project objectives<\/li><br \/><li>Provide guidance and recommendations to development teams on implementing database architecture<\/li><br \/><li>Validate business use cases for accuracy and completeness of proposed data models<\/li><br \/><li>Communicate recommendations and findings, as reports, white papers, presentations, etc.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong>Credentials Needed:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in IT-related field, master&rsquo;s degree preferred, or equivalent work experience.<\/li><br \/><li>5+ years of hands-on experience with enterprise and\/or application level data architectures.<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p><strong>Other Must Haves:<\/strong><\/p><br \/><ul><br \/><li>Excellent problem solving and troubleshooting skills.<\/li><br \/><li>Excellent communication skills.<\/li><br \/><li>Ability to reverse engineer data models from databases and existing source code<\/li><br \/><li>Experience creation and maintenance of all documentation for data models<\/li><br \/><li>Experience in creating, maintaining, and enforcing data naming conventions and database structure standards<\/li><br \/><li>Must enjoy competing in company-wide Wii bowling tournaments and having fun at work<\/li><br \/><\/ul><br \/><p>***Candidate must be able to pass background check and drug screen.<\/p>","url":"https:\/\/remoteok.io\/jobs\/66658"},{"slug":"66657-remote-cloud-solutions-architect-dito","id":"66657","epoch":"1524523832","date":"2018-04-23T15:50:32-07:00","company":"Dito","position":"Cloud Solutions Architect","tags":["architecture","cloud"],"logo":"","description":"<p>Dito is looking for a Cloud Solutions Architect to join our team! &nbsp; The position is remote so you will get to enjoy the luxuries and flexibility of working from home.&nbsp; As a Cloud Solutions Architect, the key responsibility will be to drive enterprise infrastructure, applications and analytics to public clouds while supporting the Sales team to develop and earn new business with prospects and existing customers.&nbsp; The position may be remote but our teams work together closely with you playing a crucial role in addressing &ldquo;buying&rdquo; questions that will involve the design and implementations of public and hybr